<HEADLINE>
<P>
TICKET BROKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * To malign the entire ticket brokerage industry for this year's Rose Bowl 
debacle is hugely unfair (editorial, Jan. 1). It is true that some ticket 
agencies made promises that they were unable or unwilling to keep.The people 
who bought their seats through these agencies have every right to be very 
upset, particularly if they made the trip from Wisconsin. 
</P>
<P>
 There were, however, several ticket agencies that lost a great deal of money 
ensuring that their obligations were met. Losing money is part of any 
speculative venture, which ticket brokering certainly is. 
</P>
<P>
 Ticket brokers are not inherently evil. There are people, businesses and even 
ticket brokers that are willing to lose money is order to keep their word. 
</P>
<P>
 LANCE KELLER, General Manager 
</P>
<P>
 Murray's Tickets, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
