<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; WOODBERRY LEADS NO. 3 KANSAS OVER OKLAHOMA, 94-84 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior Steve Woodberry scored 26 points and started a run midway through the 
second half as third-ranked Kansas beat Oklahoma, 94-84, Monday night in the 
Big Eight opener for both teams at Lawrence, Kan. 
</P>
<P>
 Greg Ostertag had 11 points and 14 rebounds for Kansas (16-1), which 
outrebounded Oklahoma, 57-41, and has beaten every team on the boards during 
its 12-game winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Webster scored 30 points for Oklahoma (8-4), which was scoreless during a 
three-minute stretch in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 2 Duke 89, Brown 71 -- Cherokee Parks scored 25 points and Grant Hill had 
19 to lead the Blue Devils at Durham, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
 Antonio Lang of Duke (10-0) sprained his left ankle in the first half and did 
not return. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 16 Connecticut 75, No. 18 Syracuse 67 -- Donyell Marshall had 20 points, 
11 rebounds and five blocked shots to lead the Huskies at Hartford, Conn. 
</P>
<P>
 Connecticut (13-1) is 4-0 in the Big East for the first time. Syracuse (9-2, 
2-2) lost in its first road game of the season. OTHER GAMES 
</P>
<P>
 Tecon Madden of UC Santa Barbara (7-7, 2-1) made all four of his three-point 
shots in a 53-33 Big West Conference victory over Utah State (5-8, 2-2) at 
Santa Barbara. . . . Fresno State (8-5, 3-1) withstood a late surge by New 
Mexico (11-3, 3-1) for a 69-65 Western Athletic Conference victory at Fresno. 
</P>
<P>
 Oklahoma State (11-4) recorded its 49th consecutive nonconference home victory 
with a 103-45 victory over West Texas (6-4) at Stillwater, Okla. 
</P>
