<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA ROUNDUP; MAGIC RUNS OVER THE ROCKETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shaquille O'Neal and Anfernee Hardaway each scored 28 points, and the Orlando 
Magic used a 13-0 fourth-quarter run to break open a close game and defeat the 
Houston Rockets, 115-100, Monday night at Orlando. 
</P>
<P>
 The Magic outscored the Rockets, 17-4, in the first eight minutes of the 
fourth quarter and became only the fifth team in 30 games to make at least 50% 
of its shots against the Rockets, who lead the league in field-goal defense. 
</P>
<P>
 After averaging 14 points in two games against Hakeem Olajuwon last season, 
O'Neal made 13 of 19 shots, grabbed seven rebounds and blocked one shot. 
</P>
<P>
 Olajuwon had 26 points, 11 rebounds and five blocks. 
</P>
<P>
 Tree Rollins, a Magic assistant coach who signed a 10-day contract to come out 
of retirement as a backup for O'Neal, played eight minutes and had two points, 
two rebounds, one steal and one block. 
</P>
<P>
 Philadelphia 99, Boston 94 -- Jeff Hornacek scored 31 points and had 10 
rebounds as the 76ers overcame a rally by the Celtics at Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
 Clarence Weatherspoon added 20 points and 12 rebounds for the 76ers. 
</P>
