 Toronto 3, Boston 0 -- Felix Potvin stopped 30 shots for his second shutout 
this season, and Dave Andreychuk scored two goals to lead the Maple Leafs at 
Boston. 
</P>
<P>
 Andreychuk has 34 goals -- best in the NHL. Potvin's shutout was the fourth of 
his career. 
</P>
<P>
 Montreal 4, Winnipeg 2 -- Peter Popovic scored the go-ahead goal on a power 
play seven minutes into the third period at Montreal. 
</P>
<P>
 New York Islanders 3, Ottawa 3 -- Evgeny Davydov scored early in the third 
period at Ottawa to help the Senators end the NHL's longest losing streak of 
the season at nine games. 
