<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 World Sales of Independent Films Off Slightly: Independent film companies 
generated $1.3 billion in sales in the international marketplace for the 
licensing of English language films in the year ended June 30, an American Film 
Marketing Assn. survey showed. The figure is down slightly from $1.3 billion in 
gross revenue earned in the previous fiscal year, but nonetheless was the 
second highest in the association's 14-year history. Revenue from cinemas in 
Europe and Asia were strong, but sales to video, pay and broadcast television 
fell slightly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA011194-0106 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 002980 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
