<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Standard & Poor's to Rate Bond Mutual Funds: The credit-rating company known 
for its grades on individual bonds is planning to start rating bond mutual 
funds for market risk. S&P's service comes as savers continue to pour money 
into "fixed-income" mutual funds in search of higher yields, sometimes under 
the belief that their principal is always safe. The new ratings will try to 
account for changes in interest rates, the value of the dollar and other 
factors that might hurt the prices of bonds and the mutual funds that buy them. 
</P>
