player of the Sunset League, and tonight in a ceremony before its 7 p.m. 
tip-off against fifth-ranked Fountain Valley, Huntington Beach will retire her 
jersey No. 41. . . . During her senior season, Walker averaged 20.7 points and 
14.7 rebounds per game and helped the Oilers win the league title. Now a 
redshirt freshman at Pepperdine, she is sitting out this year because of a knee 
injury but expects to make a full recovery. 
</P>
