<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: GLENDALE; POLICE SEIZE 
$2.6 MILLION IN COCAINE, ARREST 4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Glendale police Monday announced the seizure of 73 pounds of cocaine with an 
estimated street value of $2.6 million -- some of it wrapped as Christmas 
presents -- and the arrest of four suspects. 
</P>
<P>
 Scheduled to be arraigned today in Glendale Municipal Court on suspicion of 
possession of cocaine with intent to distribute are Anderson Castaneda, 35, of 
Glendale; Gabriel Garcia, 28, of Bell Gardens, and Juan Alcaraz, 22, and George 
Trevino, 26, both of Huntington Park, police spokesman Sgt. Lief Nicolaisen 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The charges stemmed from a search of Castaneda's apartment Friday during which 
police found 51 pounds of cocaine and $200,000 in cash. Several bags of cocaine 
had the word "Clinton" written on them, Nicolaisen said. 
</P>
<P>
 Castaneda had been under police surveillance for "behavior consistent with 
someone doing narcotic deals," Nicolaisen said. "Ironically, he lives pretty 
close to the police station. You can throw a rock from his apartment to the 
station." 
</P>
<P>
 After Castaneda's arrest, police went to a home in Bell Gardens, where another 
22 pounds of cocaine were found and three men were arrested, Nicolaisen said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
