<HEADLINE>
<P>
GANG VIOLENCE WOUNDS WOMAN, SON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A woman and her 5-year-old son, caught in gunfire believed to have been meant 
for someone else, were wounded Monday night west of Downtown Los Angeles in 
what police said was a gang-related shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 The child was in critical condition and undergoing surgery at Childrens 
Hospital of Los Angeles after the shooting about 7 p.m. at Pico Boulevard near 
Berendo Street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman, identified as Vicenta Chavez, was treated at Good Samaritan 
Hospital for a gunshot wound to the leg and released to visit the boy in 
Childrens Hospital. The boy's name was not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Police Department's Rampart Division would say only that a 
black Mercedes apparently was shot at. A witness said the victims were standing 
on a street corner when someone fired at a passing car and they were hit by 
random shots. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was definitely a gang thing and these people just happened to be in the 
way but, we still are working on the details and we don't have anyone in 
custody," said police Sgt. Michael Blackburn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
