AUTHENTIC FITNESS PLANS 2-FOR-1 STOCK SPLIT ON FEB. 10 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authentic Fitness, the Van Nuys-based clothing company, announced a 2-for-1 
common stock split to be distributed Feb. 10 to shareholders of record as of 
Jan. 10 
</P>
<P>
 After the split there will be 21.28 million shares outstanding. 
</P>
<P>
 The company, which sells swimwear under various brand names, including Speedo, 
has seen its profits and stock price climb in the past year. 
</P>
<P>
 The stock has recently traded in the $28 range, up from $14 at its initial 
public offering in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 The company also plans to open 40 Speed Authentic Fitness clothing stores this 
year. 
