<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BREA; 2 CRITICALLY INJURED IN 3-CAR CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men were in critical condition after one of them drove into oncoming 
traffic on Carbon Canyon Road on Monday morning and collided with two other 
vehicles, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers closed both sides of the road between Olinda Drive and the border of 
San Bernardino County for three hours while workers cleared the 8 a.m. 
collision.The accident backed up westbound traffic for several miles as 
commuters sought alternate routes into Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Louis Francisco Rodriguez, 44, of Chino Hills was eastbound when he crossed 
into the westbound lane near Olinda Drive, Sgt. Jon Strash said, adding that 
officers are checking to see if Rodriguez's driving was affected by a diabetic 
condition. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez collided with a van driven by 49-year-old Restituto Tamag and a car 
driven by 33-year-old John Williams. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams and Rodriguez were flown to UCI Medical Center in Orange, where they 
were listed in critical condition, Strash said. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams' two children, a 5-year-old and a 7-year-old, were taken to Western 
Medical Center-Santa Ana with unspecified injuries. Tamag was uninjured, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victims are all from Chino Hills, Strash said. 
</P>
