<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; MEMORABILIA-FILLED ROOM HONORS NIXON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Call it Orange County's other Richard Nixon museum. 
</P>
<P>
 It can't match the size and notoriety of Yorba Linda's Richard Nixon Library & 
Birthplace, but San Clemente's one-room exhibition does offer visitors plenty 
of information about the 37th President. 
</P>
<P>
 The President Richard Nixon Room is part of the Spanish Village Historical 
Center, in the Casa Romantica mansion on Avenida Granada. 
</P>
<P>
 The room is filled with newspaper articles, photos, political memorabilia and 
personal items that focus on Nixon's 10 years as a resident of San Clemente. 
From 1970 to 1980, his ocean-side home was known as the Western White House. 
</P>
<P>
 The display includes pictures of famous world leaders who met Nixon in San 
Clemente as well as many books authored by the former President. 
</P>
<P>
 The historical center, at 415 Avenida Granada, is open Tuesdays and Thursdays 
from 1 to 4 p.m. SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</TEXT>
