<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; REPUTED MEMBER OF GANG FATALLY SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An alleged gang member was fatally shot around midnight Monday as he was being 
driven away from a fight with rival gang members, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Eddieberto Felix, 18, of Santa Ana was in the parking lot of a Jack-In-The-Box 
restaurant at Edinger Avenue and Bristol Street when the group of men with whom 
he had been fighting opened fire, according to Lt. Bob Helton. 
</P>
<P>
 Felix ran away, flagged down a passing motorist and asked for help, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 As he was being driven away, Felix leaned out the passenger window to look 
back at the assailants and was shot once in the head, Helton said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver took Felix to the Healthcare Medical Center of Tustin, where he was 
dead on arrival, according to Helton, who said Felix was known to be a Santa 
Ana gang member. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators didn't know what the fight was about and no suspects were in 
custody Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The name of the driver, who Helton said was not involved in the dispute, was 
withheld for his safety. 
</P>
<P>
 Another shooting happened at that corner of Edinger Avenue and Bristol Street 
last year. 
</P>
<P>
 In August, Debbie Gonzalez, 23, died after a stray bullet fired during a gang 
confrontation hit her in head. A 17-year-old believed to be a gang member was 
arrested hours later on suspicion of the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzalez, who investigators said was not a gang member, had been standing with 
friends in the same parking lot of the Jack-In-The-Box when shots were fired. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect, standing on the other side of Edinger Avenue, allegedly had been 
aiming at a moving car but instead hit Gonzalez. 
</P>
</TEXT>
