GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: GLENDALE; COCAINE SEIZED, 4 SUSPECTS ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIO MORAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police on Monday announced they had seized 73 pounds of cocaine with an 
estimated street value of $2.6 million -- some of it wrapped as Christmas 
presents -- and arrested four suspects. 
</P>
<P>
 Booked on suspicion of possession of cocaine with intent to distribute were 
Anderson Castaneda, 35, of Glendale; Gabriel Garcia, 28, of Bell Gardens; and 
Juan Alcaraz, 22, and George Trevino, 26, both of Huntington Park, according to 
Glendale Police spokesman Sgt. Lief Nicolaisen. 
</P>
<P>
 All are scheduled to be arraigned today in Glendale Municipal Court, 
Nicolaisen said. 
</P>
<P>
 He said that Castaneda had been under police surveillance for "behavior 
consistent with someone doing narcotic deals. Ironically, he lives pretty close 
to the police station. You can throw a rock from his apartment to the station." 
</P>
<P>
 Police obtained a warrant to search Castaneda's apartment on North Isabel 
Street on Friday. There officers found 51 pounds of cocaine and $200,000 in 
cash, some of which was also wrapped as Christmas presents. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said plastic bags holding the cocaine smelled of diesel fuel, leading 
them to believe that the drugs were smuggled into the area in fuel tanks. 
</P>
<P>
 After Castaneda's arrest, police went to a home in the 6000 block of Gage 
Avenue in Bell Gardens, where another 22 pounds of cocaine was found and three 
men were arrested. All four suspects were arrested without incident, Nicolaisen 
said. JULIO MORAN 
</P>
