<P>
 Legal fees -- In a Dec. 4 article on a decision by the state Senate Rules 
Committee to help pay the legal defense costs of former Sen. Cecil Green, a 
committee source said that Green had been "bled dry" by legal fees in what the 
story called a "long series of lawsuits" brought by Walter E. White. The 
source's statement referred to Green's campaign committee funds, not personal 
funds. In addition, White filed two lawsuits naming Green, not "a long series." 
</P>
